 looked at the tutorial but it didn't help me at all.  Its just impossible for me to draw fingers. They always appear stiff or mutated looking, or unnaturally small.  Could somebody give me some pointers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uswordsmanjubei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swordsman Jubei</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://cgull.gamehappy.com/10x10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/1/01 5:47:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fingers</span><hr size=1> I'll give it a shot.  I'm not exactly the best when it comes to drawing hands, but once you mess aroud with it for a while you'll eventully get the hang of it.<br>
<br>
Here goes:<br>
The middle finger is roughly as long as the distance from the base of the palm to where the fingers start.<br>
Ring and index finger are about the same length, pinky goes a little further than the 3rd joint of the ring finger (that's counting the knuckle as joint #1)<br>
<br>
Important, fingers &quot;taper.&quot;  Meaning they become smaller towards the front of the finger.  Especially female fingers.  Try to make them thicker at the knuckle area than at the finger nail area (diameter wise).  Sorry if it sounds stupid. Try not to draw the finger nail in with a blatant line, show it with shades of lights and dark, or just give a hint of it.<br>
<br>
When drawing hands, it's easy to make them too small (my biggest problem when I started).  The hand as a whole almost covers your entire face if you hold it in front of you.  Its as long as the distance from chin to hairline.<br>
<br>
I like the way Pat explained drawing hands.  It's the easiest, and most reliable way I have found to draw realistic bending hands.  Start with the palm, and add little cylinders to it to take the place of the joints and bones.  That way you can get a much more realistic looking hand than any other way I can think of.<br>
Hope that helped and good luck,<br>
Sven<br>
P.S. Hands is something you just have to practice..and practice it a LOT. <p><Font Size="-1" Face="Arial"><i>The Real Folk Blues</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neosephiroth>neosephiroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/1/01 5:53:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fingers</span><hr size=1> Thanks you helped me allot. I'll go try it out ^o^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uswordsmanjubei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swordsman Jubei</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://cgull.gamehappy.com/10x10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/1/01 5:58:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fingers</span><hr size=1> You're quite welcome <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
